# Navigation Feedback Pattern

## Requirements
All clickable cards/items that navigate to new routes must:
1. Provide immediate visual feedback and prevent duplicate actions
2. **Support cmd+click / ctrl+click to open in a new tab** — this is a critical UX requirement

## The cmd+click Problem

Using `onClick` with `router.push()` breaks cmd+click (open in new tab) because the browser can only intercept that natively on `<a>` elements with an `href`. **Always use `<Link>` wrappers with `href` for navigation buttons**.

## Implementation

### Parent Component (Grid/List)
```typescript
const [isPending, startTransition] = useTransition();
const [navigatingId, setNavigatingId] = useState<string | null>(null);

const handleNavigate = (id: string, path: string) => {
  if (navigatingId) return; // Prevent duplicate clicks
  setNavigatingId(id);
  startTransition(() => router.push(path));
};
```

### Child Component — Navigation Handlers
```typescript
// Accept optional event; bail out on cmd/ctrl+click so the Link href takes over
const handleEdit = (e?: React.MouseEvent) => {
  if (e && (e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey)) return; // let <Link href> handle new-tab
  e?.preventDefault();
  if (onNavigate && !isAnyNavigating) {
    onNavigate(id, `${basePath}/edit/${id}`);
  }
};
```

### Child Component — Wrap navigation buttons in `<Link>`
```tsx
import Link from "next/link";

// Wrap each navigation IconButton in a Link for native cmd+click support.
// The onClick intercepts normal clicks to trigger loading states via router.push.
// cmd/ctrl+click skips preventDefault and the href opens natively in a new tab.
<Link href={`${basePath}/edit/${id}`} tabIndex={-1} onClick={(e) => { e.stopPropagation(); handleEdit(e); }}>
  <IconButton
    icon={Pencil}
    tooltip={isDisabled ? "Please wait..." : "Edit"}
    size="sm"
    variant="ghost"
    disabled={isDisabled}
  />
</Link>
```

### Card body with no primary URL (opens a modal on click)
```typescript
// For cards that open a modal on click (no single primary URL),
// handle cmd/ctrl+click explicitly to open the most relevant destination.
const handleCardClick = (e: React.MouseEvent) => {
  if (e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey) {
    window.open(`${basePath}/run/${id}`, "_blank");
    return;
  }
  // normal click — open modal
  setIsActionModalOpen(true);
};
```

### Child Component — Loading Overlay
```typescript
const isDisabled = isNavigating || isAnyNavigating;

{isNavigating && (
  <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-background/80 backdrop-blur-sm z-20 flex items-center justify-center">
    <Loader2 className="w-8 h-8 text-primary animate-spin" />
  </div>
)}
```

## Checklist
- ✅ `useTransition` + `startTransition` for navigation
- ✅ Navigation buttons wrapped in `<Link href={...}>` for cmd+click support
- ✅ Handler accepts `(e?: React.MouseEvent)` and returns early on `e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey`
- ✅ Loading overlay with spinner on active card
- ✅ Disable all cards when any is navigating
- ✅ Prevent duplicate clicks with state check
- ✅ Update tooltips/aria-labels to "Please wait..."
- ✅ Card body with modal: handle `e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey` with `window.open`